docs.abstract: Rattled by tech’s latest trend, businesses have turned to advisers at Boston Consulting Group, McKinsey and KPMG for guidance on adopting generative artificial intelligence.
docs.snippet: Rattled by tech’s latest trend, businesses have turned to advisers at Boston Consulting Group, McKinsey and KPMG for guidance on adopting generative artificial intelligence.
docs.lead_paragraph: After ChatGPT came out in 2022, the marketing team at Reckitt Benckiser, which makes Lysol and Mucinex, was convinced that new artificial intelligence technology could help its business. But the team was uncertain about how, so it turned to Boston Consulting Group for help.

headline.main: The A.I. Boom Has an Unlikely Early Winner: Wonky Consultants
headline.print_headline: Consulting Firms Cash In on Businesses’ Need for A.I. Guidance

docs.abstract: She made significant contributions at IBM, but she lost her job because of her conviction that she inhabited the wrong body. She later fought for transgender rights.
docs.snippet: She made significant contributions at IBM, but she lost her job because of her conviction that she inhabited the wrong body. She later fought for transgender rights.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lynn Conway, a pioneering computer scientist who was fired by IBM in the 1960s after telling managers that she was transgender, despite her significant technological innovations — and who received a rare formal apology from the company 52 years later — died on June 9 in Jackson, Mich. She was 86.

headline.main: Lynn Conway, Computing Pioneer and Transgender Advocate, Dies at 86
headline.print_headline: Lynn Conway, Computing Pioneer and Transgender Advocate, Dies at 86
